page.title: 01GENERAL REVIEW OF WEMBLEY
page.content:
Most of our block is in the{London {Borough of Brent,}with a small area in the south-west corner,in L.B.Ealing.
The area is predominantly residential with most of the houses being built in the 1930's of two- storey,terraced or semi-detached construction.There are also a few light-industrial estates producing mainly small components.
The world famous {Wembley Stadium}is also within our area, along with the Wembley Arena and Conference Centre.
Passing through we have sections of the {Grand Union Canal,}the main { {London-Euston Railway}line to Scotland,the{A40}( London to Fishguard via Oxford ) and the {North Circular roads.
